comment update: <>

How to display images by w3m on the remote host. (Experimental)

* Requirement
  (Xlib, Framebuffer)
  gdk-pixbuf >= 2.14
  gvfs or curl

  (Win32)
  GDI+
  URL Monikers

* Installation
  o mlterm >= 3.1.7
    ./configure ... (--enable-sixel option is necessary for mlterm 3.1.8 or before)
    make
    make install

  o w3m 0.5.3
    tar xzvf w3m-0.5.3.tar.gz ; cd w3m-0.5.3
    patch -p1 < w3m-0.5.3-remoteimg.patch
    ./configure --enable-image ...
    make
    make install

o Usage
  w3m -ri http://...
